	<h1>Safety Tips for Street Dogs</h1>

	<p>Street dogs can be found in many cities around the world. While they may seem friendly and harmless, they can also be dangerous if they feel threatened or cornered. Here are some tips to help you stay safe around street dogs:</p>

	<h2>1. Don't approach street dogs</h2>
	<p>Even if they seem friendly, it's best to avoid approaching street dogs. They may feel threatened or scared and react by biting or attacking.</p>

	<h2>2. Avoid eye contact</h2>
	<p>Eye contact can be seen as a threat by street dogs. If you encounter a street dog, avoid making direct eye contact and try to slowly back away.</p>

	<h2>3. Don't run away</h2>
	<p>If a street dog starts to approach you, don't run away. This can trigger their instinct to chase and attack. Instead, try to stay calm and slowly back away.</p>

	<h2>4. Stay still if a dog attacks</h2>
	<p>If a street dog attacks you, try to stay still and protect your face and neck. Don't try to fight back or run away, as this can make the dog more aggressive. Wait for the dog to lose interest and slowly back away.</p>

	<h2>5. Carry a dog deterrent spray</h2>
	<p>If you're in an area with a lot of street dogs, consider carrying a dog deterrent spray. This can be used to scare away aggressive dogs and give you time to escape.</p>

	<h2>6. Don't disturb a sleeping dog</h2>
	<p>If you see a street dog sleeping, avoid disturbing it. They may become aggressive if they feel threatened while sleeping.</p>

	<h2>7. Report aggressive dogs to authorities</h2>
	<p>If you encounter an aggressive street dog, report it to local authorities. This can help prevent future attacks and keep the community safe.</p>

	

	<p>By following these safety tips, you can help protect yourself and stay safe around street dogs.</p>
